description:
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have completed the Diploma in Health and Social Care Level 3 or equivalent. Candidates must also have Literacy and Numeracy level 2 or equivalent and must complete the Trust Healthcare Assistant competencies within their probationary period (first 6 months in role).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates who do not have the required qualifications will be expected to enrol on the Healthcare Assistant Framework which will include the acquisition of the level 3 Diploma Health and Social Care, level 2 in Literacy and Numeracy or equivalent and achievement of competencies. You will have a maximum of 2 years to complete this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Durham and Darlington Adult Mental Health Services are continuing to develop urgent care responses within the locality. As a part of this we have successfully bid to provide a &#39;help line&#39; service to members of the public who may be experiencing mental health symptoms or have concerns about their mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting and important addition to our existing urgent care provision within the locality, and it is anticipated will be a well utilised point of support and contact by members of the public, health care professionals and other agencies. It will provide a much needed point of contact for individuals who may not feel they need &#39;crisis&#39; interventions but have concerns about their mental well being, and are seeking additional information or advice as to where they can access support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for highly motivated applicants who want to make a difference to others at the point they contact services seeking advice and support. You will have excellent interpersonal skills, be compassionate, calm and able to capture key information from callers. Utilising the training you will be provided with, you will be confident in managing initial triage conversations and signposting to appropriate services and/or providing relevant information to callers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be working as part of a team across this 24 hour/7 day a week service and working closely with other teams who provide urgent care within the Trust - such as Crisis Teams, Liaison and Street Triage services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will need to demonstrate the ability to work on their own initiative, and to work flexibly and co-operatively as part of a team. They will also benefit from having worked within a customer service environment, though this is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key elements of the role will be to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the first point of contact for patients, health care professionals, partner agencies and other callers provide basic support and health information to people accessing the service, including basic triage of risk/needs and safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver safe, high quality effective healthcare over the telephone using standard processes and in accordance with your knowledge, skills and training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See job description for complete information regarding duties and responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Burke, Service Manager - 07585100288&lt;/p&gt;
